            <h1>Equality</h1>
            <div class="temaMobIngressImg" style="display: none;"><img src="/Upload/PORTAL/Temabilder/likestilling_150x113.jpg" alt="Men and women talking together" /></div>
            <p class="textIngress">The Government will combat all forms of discrimination. Everyone has a right to self-development and to utilise his/her abilities and live his/her own life, irrespective of gender, social background, religion, sexual orientation, disability or ethnic background.</p>
            <img src="/Upload/PORTAL/Temabilder/likestilling_150x113.jpg" alt="Men and women talking together" class="temaIngressImg" />
            <div class="descriptionText"><p><em>The Ministry of Children and Equality</em> is responsible for coordinating the Government’s family and equality policies and legislation in this area. <em>The Ministry of Labour and Social Inclusion</em> is responsible for immigration and asylum policy and for the policy towards the Sami people and minorities.<br />&nbsp;<br />On this page you will find general information and documents that relate to equality. You can explore this topic in more detail by using the menu on the right.<br /></p></div>
